---
import Screenshot from './Screenshot.astro';
---

<section class="std" id="branch">
  <div class="frame">
    <div class="section-tag reveal">02 · Branching as a workflow</div>
    <h2 class="h-section section-h reveal">
      A good frame is a <span class="em">starting point.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="section-lede reveal">
      Locking the parent and fanning out children is how visual ideas actually develop.
      ima2-gen makes it the default.
    </p>
    <div class="branch-grid">
      <div class="branch-shot reveal">
        <Screenshot
          src="screenshots/node-mode.png"
          alt="ima2-gen Node mode canvas with a parent node and child branches showing palette, framing, and copy variants."
          aspect="4/3"
          eager
        />
      </div>
      <ol class="scenarios reveal" aria-label="Branching scenario steps">
        <li>
          <span class="step">01</span>
          <div class="body">
            <strong>Generate a parent.</strong> A frame you actually want to keep.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step">02</span>
          <div class="body">
            <strong>Fan out children.</strong> Palette swap, tighter crop, alternate copy
            margin — three nodes, three runs.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step">03</span>
          <div class="body">
            <strong>Compare without loss.</strong> The parent stays. Children recover by
            request ID even after a refresh.
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .branch-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr;
    gap: 56px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .scenarios {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .scenarios li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 14px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 18px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .scenarios li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .scenarios .step {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--accent);
    padding-top: 2px;
    min-width: 32px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .scenarios .body {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .scenarios .body strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .branch-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; }
    .scenarios .body { font-size: 15px; }
  }
</style>
